<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>96927</id>
    <title>Imported Data (image) remains as trash in document - File size not reduced after removal</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">LibreOffice Writer saves background image in document, but does not remove it, after deletion or change, which can lead to massive document filesizes.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">1 Format &gt; Page &gt; Area &gt; Fill &gt; Bitmap &gt; Import Graphic (choose any .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">jpg or .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">png)</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">2 Apply, and notice the larger filesize (image has been saved in document)</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.6">3 Reset Page Fill to Blank or None</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.7">4 Notice the filesize does not reduce!</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.8">The image remains inside the document.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.9">5 Repeat steps, import new graphic</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Result: Filesizes of 10+mb for a single page document can be the result, if users tries three different background images (just an example).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
